Sec. 147.029. INSOLVENCY OF SURETY. If the county judge
discovers that the surety on a bond is insolvent or determines that
the surety is financially unable to make the bond sufficient, the
county judge shall notify the commission merchant and the commission
merchant shall execute a new bond in accordance with the requirements
for the original bond.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1381, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

